      • getPasswordProperty

        public String getPasswordProperty​(String name,
                                  String service)
        Returns the decoded value associated with an encrypted property, or null if the property has no value and it has not an associated registered MkvProperty, or its value can't be decoded. This method expects the data to be encrypted with the same algorithm used for passwords; likewise, the input format must be the same, e.g. ":AC 9C 71 51 6F 14 B4 85" for string "mkvpwd" If the property value doesn't start with ':' its value is returned verbatim.
        Parameters:
        name - the property name.
        service - the service name used to encrypt the value with pwdtool.
        Returns:
        the value associated with the specified property, or null if the property has no value and it has not an associated registered MkvProperty, or its value can't be decoded.

        public boolean setProperty​(String name,
                           String value)
                    throws MkvException
        Overrides the user-defined value for a property.

        This function should be used only in exceptional circumstance, in order to keep configuration tracking easier.

        Parameters:
        name - the property name.
        value - the property value.
        Returns:
        false if the specified value has not been accepted.
        Throws:
        MkvException - if the specified value has an invalid format.

      • getServicePassword

        public boolean getServicePassword​(String serviceName,
                                  MkvServicePasswordListener listener)
        Retrieve a password configuration for the specified service, communicating with the Daemon Password Server to get it safely and securely over the encrypted registration channel. The value of the password is notified asynchronously to the application using the provided listener. This method should be called after REGISTER_IDLE has been delivered.
        Parameters:
        serviceName - the service to retrieve the password for
        listener - the callback listener for the result
        Returns:
        true in case of success posting the request, false in case of any failure
